      "id": "getting-started"
    }}>{`Getting Started`}</h2>
    <p>{`Getting started is easy. Simply add this component to your pipeline:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-toml",
        "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
        "title": "\"vector.toml\""
      }}>{`[transforms.tag_protection]
  type = "tag_cardinality_limit"
  inputs = ["my-source-id"]
  limit_exceeded_action = "drop_tag"
  mode = "exact"
  value_limit = 500
`}</code></pre>
    <CodeExplanation mdxType="CodeExplanation">
      <ul>
        <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`limit_exceeded_action`}</inlineCode>{` described the behavior when the `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`value_limit`}</inlineCode>{` is reached.`}</li>
        <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`mode`}</inlineCode>{` enables you to switch between `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`exact`}</inlineCode>{` and `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`probabilistic`}</inlineCode>{` algorithms to trade performance for memory efficiency.`}</li>
        <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`value`}</inlineCode>{` limit allows you to select exactly how many unique tag values you're willing to accept.`}</li>
      </ul>
